refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arrayarray_intersect_uassoc arrayarray arrayarrays callablekey_compare_func
array_intersect_uassoc returns an array containing all the values of array that are present in all the arguments. Note that the keys are used in the comparison unlike in array_intersect.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns the values of array whose values exist
 in all of the arguments.

  &reftitle.examples;



    array_intersect_uassoc example


<?php
$array1 = array("a" => "green", "b" => "brown", "c" => "blue", "red");
$array2 = array("a" => "GREEN", "B" => "brown", "yellow", "red");

print_r(array_intersect_uassoc($array1, $array2, "strcasecmp"));
?>


    &example.outputs;


Array
(
    [b] => brown
)
